{"id": "EUVD-2024-42875", "enisaUuid": "114fbed8-b59a-3c6c-9f35-6a9aede5f262", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndma-debug: fix a possible deadlock on radix_lock\n\nradix_lock() shouldn't be held while holding dma_hash_entry[idx].lock\notherwise, there's a possible deadlock scenario when\ndma debug API is called holding rq_lock():\n\nCPU0                   CPU1                       CPU2\ndma_free_attrs()\ncheck_unmap()          add_dma_entry()            __schedule() //out\n                                                  (A) rq_lock()\nget_hash_bucket()\n(A) dma_entry_hash\n                                                  check_sync()\n                       (A) radix_lock()           (W) dma_entry_hash\ndma_entry_free()\n(W) radix_lock()\n                       // CPU2's one\n                       (W) rq_lock()\n\nCPU1 situation can happen when it extending radix tree and\nit tries to wake up kswapd via wake_all_kswapd().\n\nCPU2 situation can happen while perf_event_task_sched_out()\n(i.e. dma sync operation is called while deleting perf_event using\n etm and etr tmc which are Arm Coresight hwtracing driver backends).\n\nTo remove this possible situation, call dma_entry_free() after\nput_hash_bucket() in check_unmap().", "datePublished": "2025-01-11T12:25:13", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T20:39:31", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3ccce34a5c3f5c9541108a451657ade621524b32", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/efe1b9bbf356357fdff0399af361133d6e3ba18e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8c1b4fea8d62285f5e1a8194889b39661608bd8a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c212d91070beca0d03fef7bf988baf4ff4b3eee4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f2b95248a16c5186d1c658fc0aeb2f3bd95e5259", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7543c3e3b9b88212fcd0aaf5cab5588797bdc7de", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-47143", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00001.html", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00002.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-47143"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "02ec48da-023b-33be-84f2-af837236ae74", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.174"}, {"id": "4caa8a34-47c9-335d-ad3c-e073fd0ecdb3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <8c1b4fea8d62285f5e1a8194889b39661608bd8a"}, {"id": "4cc9ed4a-0d2f-3f42-96a0-55214dd6c092", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <f2b95248a16c5186d1c658fc0aeb2f3bd95e5259"}, {"id": "5f5f8598-176c-3e58-a51b-1276f206c084", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <c212d91070beca0d03fef7bf988baf4ff4b3eee4"}, {"id": "63b8322d-5698-37d1-a4a1-31140414c263", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.5"}, {"id": "7f749588-43a2-3fa6-b57b-286f262b7096", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.66"}, {"id": "afadcf03-3d41-3854-bb17-c589caca4314", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "b4569228-a6b6-3880-be9c-7bda1f514705", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.120"}, {"id": "ce6eae5a-5995-3de1-9dda-4bb1b3bb1e8a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <3ccce34a5c3f5c9541108a451657ade621524b32"}, {"id": "ddbf5829-8b88-32b8-96d1-44b700b6919e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <efe1b9bbf356357fdff0399af361133d6e3ba18e"}, {"id": "fdd311d4-c3cb-32dc-bfff-8ebc4d7e0ab1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.231"}, {"id": "fedbc3ce-80e9-3141-9bdf-a4ec1dd9b311", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <7543c3e3b9b88212fcd0